        boolean allowsTraverseNode​(long... labels)
        true if a particular node with exactly these labels can be traversed.
        Parameters:
        labels - the labels on the node to be checked. If labels only contains TokenConstants.ANY_LABEL it will work the same as allowsTraverseAllLabels()

      • allowsTraverseRelType

        boolean allowsTraverseRelType​(int relType)
        true if the relType can be traversed.
        Parameters:
        relType - the relationship type to check access for. If relType is TokenConstants.ANY_RELATIONSHIP_TYPE it will work the same as allowsTraverseAllRelTypes()

      • shouldBoostAccessForProcedureWith

        @Deprecated
boolean shouldBoostAccessForProcedureWith​(String[] allowed)
        Deprecated.
        use allowsExecuteProcedure(int) and shouldBoostProcedure(int) instead
        Determines whether this mode allows execution of a procedure with the parameter string array in its procedure annotation.
        Parameters:
        allowed - An array of strings that encodes permissions that allows the execution of a procedure
        Returns:
        true if this mode allows the execution of a procedure with the given parameter string array encoding permission

      • shouldBoostProcedure

        boolean shouldBoostProcedure​(int procedureId)
        Check if execution of a procedure should be done with boosted privileges.

        Note: this does not check if execution is allowed

        Parameters:
        procedureId - id of the procedure
        Returns:
        true if the procedure with this id should be executed with boosted privileges
